From 71270be2f6b56de28c32e321860ca40aed68b690 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shayne Chen <shayne.chen@mediatek.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 19:37:01 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] mtk: mac80211: fix __ieee80211_link_copy_chanctx_to_vlans()
 warning
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Problem: 
The following warning trace happens on doing wifi down while the CAC
countdown hasn't finished yet.
[  503.244931]  __ieee80211_link_copy_chanctx_to_vlans+0x12c/0x140 [mac80211]
[  503.244972]  ieee80211_link_copy_chanctx_to_vlans+0xc/0x18 [mac80211]
[  503.245012]  ieee80211_stop_ap+0x2b4/0x4a8 [mac80211]

Root Cause: 
A normal link BSS disabled flow is:
ieee80211_stop_ap
...
ieee80211_link_copy_chanctx_to_vlans
ieee80211_link_release_channel

However, if there's still doing CAC countdown, the flow becomes:
cfg80211_stop_radar_detection
ieee80211_end_cac
ieee80211_link_release_channel
ieee80211_stop_ap
...
ieee80211_link_copy_chanctx_to_vlans
ieee80211_link_release_channel

In the CAC case, ieee80211_link_release_channel is executed before
ieee80211_link_copy_chanctx_to_vlans, causing the warning trace.

Solution: 
Fix this by only doing the CAC ieee80211_link_release_channel if it's a
bootup CAC. Otherwise, leave the channel release to ieee80211_stop_ap.

Feature:
DFS

Signed-off-by: Shayne Chen <shayne.chen@mediatek.com>
---
 net/mac80211/cfg.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/cfg.c b/net/mac80211/cfg.c
index 09809d7a..73d11d2e 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/cfg.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/cfg.c
@@ -3998,7 +3998,8 @@ static void ieee80211_end_cac(struct wiphy *wiphy,
 					  &link_data->dfs_cac_timer_work);
 
 		if (sdata->wdev.links[link_id].cac_started) {
-			ieee80211_link_release_channel(link_data);
+			if (!sdata->wdev.links[link_id].ap.beacon_interval)
+				ieee80211_link_release_channel(link_data);
 			sdata->wdev.links[link_id].cac_started = false;
 		}
 	}
